                    "answer": "Modern LFP batteries are warrantied for 10-15 years or 4,000-6,000 cycles. In practice, expect 12-15 years of useful life before capacity degrades below 70%. This is significantly better than older NMC chemistry (Powerwall 2) which degraded faster."
